        "content": "<p>cataggar edited <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12774\">issue #12774</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I need a way to more easily acquire wasmtime binaries. In #7192, I asked about distributing via npm, but I recently started using <a href=\"https://just.systems/man/en/\">just </a> a lot. One of the easiest ways to acquire it in Docker or a WSL or any new environment with Python is to do </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">tdnf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">install</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">python3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">python3</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">pip</span>\n<span class=\"n\">python3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pip</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">install</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">uv</span>\n<span class=\"n\">echo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PATH</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s\">\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bashrc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">source</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bashrc</span>\n<span class=\"n\">uv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">install</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span